DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Chicago Public Library\\nCost: free\\nAges: 0-60 mo
 nths\\nCategory: Film & Events\\n\\nJoin us for the highly acclaimed roman
 tic comedy/fantasy The Princess Bride to celebrate the late\, great Rob Re
 iner. In the delightfully fractured tale\, a grandfather reads a story abo
 ut a beautiful young woman named Buttercup to his bored grandson. Then\, t
 he audience is magically transported into the tale\, complete with villain
 s\, creepy creatures\, offbeat adventure and one beautiful love story. Fea
 turing an all-star cast\, Rob Reiner's masterpiece is for all ages and one
  of the best films of the\\n\\nMore info: https://chipublib.bibliocommons.
 com/events/6983a58f94297d3600a9f991
LOCATION:Rogers Park\, 6907 N. Clark St.\, Chicago\, IL 60626
URL:https://chipublib.bibliocommons.com/events/6983a58f94297d3600a9f991
