SUMMARY:Dozin' with the Dinos
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260410T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260411T090000
DTSTAMP:20260401T160715Z
UID:dddbe97529c75e915053e8e8243bb856@family-events-agent
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:museum,science,family,families,kids_families
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Field Museum - Events\\nCost: Ticket required\\nCat
 egory: General\\n\\nSee the Field Museum in a whole new light! Families an
 d groups with kids ages 6 to 12 can spend the night at the museum during D
 ozin' with the Dinos. Stay up late with scientists as the Field Museum com
 es to life in games\, challenges\, and stories throughout the night. Will 
 you dissect owl pellets and identify animal tracks to become the next grea
 t wildlife detective? Or\, will you embark on a paleontologist's expeditio
 n to learn how fossils form? Take on these adventures and more with the Do
 zin’ Institute for Nocturnal Observations (DINO) on our late-night missi
 on of discovery. Then\, grab your flashlight and explore the halls as the 
 lights go out. This is a night at the museum you won't forget!\\n\\nMore i
 nfo: https://www.fieldmuseum.org/our-events/dozin-with-the-dinos/dozin-04-
 10-2026
LOCATION:Field Museum\, 1400 S Lake Shore Dr\, Chicago\, IL 60605
URL:https://www.fieldmuseum.org/our-events/dozin-with-the-dinos/dozin-04-1
 0-2026
